    -- 1. Forward map is a function (trivial)
    -- 2. Inverse map is a function (trivial)
    -- 3. Composing the maps gives the identity
    --   - (f ↦ B_f) ∘ (B_f ↦ f) = id
    --   - (B_f ↦ f) ∘ (f ↦ B_f) = id
```

The proof of these conditions is standard for the characteristic function:

```tactics
    -- Prove the forward direction is a function
